description.narrative: Policies, standards and service packages are in place to ensure quality and up-to-date, family-centred maternal, newborn, child and adolescent care, with a focus on disparity reduction., which contributes to Child Health, Early Childhood Development, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Children and adolescents benefit from increased utilization of equitable, quality health and nutrition services, and have practices that promote their health, well-being, safety and green living.
